The U.N.-sponsored climate conference, so far characterized by defiant postures and mutual recriminations, caught renewed attention on Friday with the release of a document outlining ambitious greenhouse gas reductions over the next 40 years, with industrialized nations bearing the bulk of the burden on their shoulders in the short term.
