The current battle is both to save individual economies and to save the planet, with China and the United States clashing over their respective obligations, while the poorest nations insist that the world’s twenty-four most influential countries are ignoring the scientific imperative to take the boldest action.
Ricardo Ulate, a delegate from Costa Rica, said it’s not surprising that major powers are discussing who should pay for spending to limit greenhouse gases, even as vulnerable countries have become more aggressive in seeking to hold big emitters accountable for their actions.
