Turkish justice dissolves pro-Kurdish party, a decision with serious consequences
Turkey's Constitutional Court ruled on Friday in favor of the dissolution of the country's main pro-Kurdish party, a decision that immediately sparked anger in the Kurdish community, in the southeast of the country and in Istanbul.
